# Max agents + Auto model (Radio Udaan)

When the user says **go ahead**, **max agents**, or assigns a **multi-layer task** (WP plugin + Flutter, new tab/screen, API + UI):

## Coordinator (parent)

1. Read `.cursor/memory/*` and project rules first.
2. Split into **parallel** Task sub-agents when work is independent.
3. **Merge** sub-agent output; resolve conflicts; run smoke checks (`php -l`, `dart analyze lib`, curl key endpoints).
4. Update `.cursor/memory/` when APIs or behavior change.
5. Do **not** commit unless the user asks.

## Sub-agents (Task tool)

| Rule | Requirement |
|------|-------------|
| **Model** | **Always** `model: fast` (Cursor **Auto**). No sub-agent may use Opus/Sonnet/other unless the user **explicitly** names an allowed model slug. |
| **Role** | Senior specialist (20+ years) in the task domain. |
| **Rules** | Follow all workspace rules: coding-standards, performance, store-compliance, project-context, memory system. |
| **Paths** | Absolute paths under `/Users/nexus/Documents/Radio Udan`. |
| **Return** | Files changed, acceptance criteria pass/fail, verification commands run. |

## Parallel split pattern (example: Library YouTube)

| Agent | Owns |
|-------|------|
| WP `generalPurpose` | YouTube Data API proxy, REST routes, admin settings, transients |
| Flutter `generalPurpose` | Library tab UI, playlists/search/player/bookmarks |
| `shell` (optional) | `php -l`, `dart analyze`, curl smoke scripts |

## Do not

- Run sub-agents without `model: fast` on this project (user mandate).
- Skip delegation for large UI+API features.
- Assume sub-agent work is merged — parent verifies in repo.
